---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Blog">
  <article class="blog-post">
    <h1 class="blog-title">Gathering Figs</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A memory of Pappou and the garden</p>
    
    <div class="blog-content">
      <p>My feet were carefully placed in the stable crevices of the long smooth limbs of the tree; while I was normally scared of heights, the feeling of something alive supporting me gave me comfort. I reached forward, eyeing a fig whose plump green skin was slowly tearing away from the red and white flesh. I twisted the stem to release it from the branch, and dropped it into the basket below.</p>
      
      <p>My Pappou, my grandfather, gave a sharp nod of approval up at me, while hooking his gnarled cane around another branch to bring it down for further inspection. I listened to his advice earnestly, wanting to preserve his ways. When the basket was full, I gently slipped down from the tree; the red soil was laden with hay and plastered with a mush of ant-ridden figs.</p>

      <p>Pappou smooths the wispy white strands that barely shield his tanned bald head. He picks up a fig and peels it with his fingers; the swirls and creases of his calloused hands are caked with dirt, his nails are dull and strong. He waved me over and handed me a half. A thin white skin covered the pink flesh; it was chewy and sweet with a slight crunch from the seeds...</p>
      </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .blog-post { max-width: 700px; margin: 4rem auto; background: white; padding: 4rem; }
  .blog-title {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .subtitle { text-align: center; color: var(--muted-teal); margin-bottom: 3rem; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; }
  .blog-content p { font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; text-indent: 2rem; }
</style>